<%#
  # Pet Update — Turbo Stream response (SUCCESS path)
  #
  # Rendered by PetsController#update after @pet.update succeeds, when the
  # request wants a Turbo Stream (Turbo sets that Accept header on form
  # submissions automatically). On failure the controller instead re-renders
  # :edit with a 422, which lands back in the "drawer" frame so errors show in
  # the still-open modal — that path does NOT come through this file.
  #
  # What this does: surgically swaps the Identity card already on the page with
  # a freshly-rendered one — no full reload. Streams target by DOM id anywhere
  # in the document, so it doesn't matter that the card lives inside the
  # pet_content frame.
  #
  # CRITICAL: the dom_id below MUST match the id on the partial's root element
  #   (see _pet_identity_card.html.erb). If the prefixes drift apart, Turbo
  #   finds no target, does nothing, and still returns 200 — a silent no-op.
  #   Using dom_id on both sides keeps the format identical; keep the prefix
  #   (:pet_identity_card) identical too.
  #
  # The modal closing is handled separately by popup_controller.js (it hides on
  # turbo:submit-end success) — this stream only refreshes the card.
%>
<%= turbo_stream.replace dom_id(@pet, :pet_identity_card),
      partial: "pets/pet_identity_card", locals: { pet: @pet } %>
